<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6AFFE9FFA54B658073FCFCFDA3" authority="Lafresnaye, 1847" authorityName="Lafresnaye" authorityYear="1847" box="[356,798,583,608]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Tachyphonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="delatrii">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFBFFE9FFA54B658073FDB2FDA3" box="[356,592,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Tachyphonus delatrii</emphasis>
Lafresnaye, 1847
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3506562FFE9FFA54AC68058FF12FD64" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF536E9FFE9FFA54AC68058FF12FD64" blockId="7.[151,1436,548,968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">
Included species. Monospecific; includes only 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6AFFE9FFA548DE8058FC04FD46" box="[735,998,620,645]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Chrysocorypha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="delatrii">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFBFFE9FFA548DE8058FC04FD46" box="[735,998,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Chrysocorypha delatrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, currently recognized as 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6AFFE9FFA54F088058FF08FD6B" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Tachyphonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="delatrii">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFBFFE9FFA54F088058FF08FD6B" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Tachyphonus delatrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3506562FFE9FFA54AC68080FAB4FD0F" box="[199,1366,692,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BF536E9FFE9FFA54AC68080FAB4FD0F" blockId="7.[151,1436,548,968]" box="[199,1366,692,717]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">
Diagnosis. This genus is diagnosed by the specific characters of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6AFFE9FFA549988080FAB0FD0F" authority="Lafresnaye, 1847" authorityName="Lafresnaye" authorityYear="1847" box="[921,1362,692,717]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Tachyphonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="delatrii">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFBFFE9FFA549988080FB67FD0E" box="[921,1157,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Tachyphonus delatrii</emphasis>
Lafresnaye, 1847
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3506562FFE9FFA54AC680E3FC66FCD7" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF536E9FFE9FFA54AC680E3FC66FCD7" blockId="7.[151,1436,548,968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Etymology. The name, feminine in gender, is formed from the Greek χρυσός, “gold,” and Greek κορυφή, “crown” or “top of the head,” in allusion to the male’s tawny crest.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3506562FFE9FFA54AC68114FD64FC04" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF536E9FFE9FFA54AC68114FD64FC04" blockId="7.[151,1436,548,968]" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">
Comments. As explained in the previous section, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6AFFE9FFA548FB812BFC0AFCFB" box="[762,1000,799,824]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Tachyphonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="delatrii">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFBFFE9FFA548FB812BFC0AFCFB" box="[762,1000,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Tachyphonus delatrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms a strongly supported clade with 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6AFFE9FFA54A968171FECAFC9F" box="[151,296,837,860]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Tachyphonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="surinamus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFBFFE9FFA54A968171FECAFC9F" box="[151,296,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">T. surinamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6AFFE9FFA54B378171FE95FC9F" box="[310,375,837,860]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Lanio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFBFFE9FFA54B378171FE95FC9F" box="[310,375,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Lanio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6AFFE9FFA54BB78170FDB6FC9E" box="[438,596,836,861]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Rhodospingus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFBFFE9FFA54BB78170FDB6FC9E" box="[438,596,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Rhodospingus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13712A6CFFE9FFA548678170FD48FC9E" box="[614,682,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[466,1121,203,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[461,1125,193,1912]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Maximum clade credibility tree from the Bayesian analyses of Burns et al. (2014). Subfamilies Coerebinae and Tachyphoninae shown. Labeling and format as in Fig. 1." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266313/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). As is the case with 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6AFFE9FFA5499C8171FBCFFC9F" box="[925,1069,837,860]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Tachyphonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="surinamus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFBFFE9FFA5499C8171FBCFFC9F" box="[925,1069,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">T. surinamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, molecular phylogenies indicate that 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6AFFE9FFA54AC6815CFED7FC43" box="[199,309,871,896]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Tachyphonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="delatrii">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFBFFE9FFA54AC6815CFED7FC43" box="[199,309,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">T. delatrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not closely related to any one of these species in particular. Thus, unless a broad and exceptionally heterogeneous genus subsumes all six species involved, a new generic name is needed for 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6AFFE9FFA54E8F81B9FB1EFC66" box="[1166,1276,908,933]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Tachyphonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="delatrii">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFBFFE9FFA54E8F81B9FB1EFC66" box="[1166,1276,908,933]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">T. delatrii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Accordingly, we provide 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6AFFE9FFA54B1A819BFE2AFC0B" box="[283,456,943,968]" class="Aves" family="Thraupidae" genus="Chrysocorypha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="336" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFBFFE9FFA54B1A819BFE2AFC0B" box="[283,456,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="336">Chrysocorypha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for this purpose.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
